From: uphrrmk@gemini.oscs.montana.edu (Jack Coyote)
Crossposted-To: comp.os.linux.help
Subject: Re: acm won't run!  It compiled ine!
Date: 18 Oct 1993 22:17:37 GMT
Reply-To: uphrrmk@gemini.oscs.montana.edu (Jack Coyote)

In comp.os.linux.misc, rbrewer@psu.edu writes:

>Hi all.  I've been trying to run acm 3.1 on my linux machine.
>It compiles fine, and I can start up the server.  However, 
>as soon as a client connects to the server, the server dies
>with a floating point exception.  Does anyone have any
>hints for getting this running?


I got it working after I noticed that two of the structures have elements
called *.index .  One of the #define's somewhere redefines this to something
else, which causes a core dump.

The offending structures are a color structure in Vlib.h (?) and the craft
structure in pm.h .

I just pumped the whole tree through a sed script ('s/\.index/\.mydex/g').

Then I started wasting lots of time.   =)

